{{ 'ka-journal-card.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

{%- comment -%}
  K&A Journal Grid — Docs/journal-build-spec.md §3 A5, §7 Flags J6/J7.

  Real, dynamic Shopify blog.articles — NOT the 7 invented placeholder
  cards shown in Prototypes/journal-index-v1.html. Those cards are
  explicitly flagged in the build spec (§5 Content Requirements) as
  "entirely invented, in K&A's house voice, for layout demonstration
  only" and "must not be treated as a content-production task list
  without Karishma & Ashita's explicit sign-off." Hardcoding them here
  as if they were live articles would mean shipping fake dead-end
  content (no real article resource, no real URL) on the production
  site — a content-integrity problem, not just a fidelity shortcut.
  This is a deliberate, flagged deviation from a literal reproduction
  of the prototype; see this build's handoff notes.

  Instead: this grid loops the REAL blog (whatever currently exists —
  today that's the 1 new live article plus the 3 already-published
  2024 articles that start rendering correctly the moment this
  template exists, per the spec's own audit in §0/§1). The category
  taxonomy (J2), featured-story exclusion (J3), read-time computation
  (J4), empty-category state (J6) and native pagination (J7) are all
  fully built and will hold at real scale the moment more articles are
  written and tagged — proving the system works without fabricating
  content to demonstrate it.

  Featured-article exclusion: mirrors the exact selection logic in
  sections/ka-journal-featured.liquid (tag "featured", else most
  recent) so whichever article renders there is never duplicated here.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- comment -%}
  featured_article lookup mirrors sections/ka-journal-featured.liquid's
  identical logic exactly (kept outside this section's own {% paginate
  %} block below — see that file's header comment for why a second,
  unrelated paginate block is deliberately avoided on this same page).
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign featured_article = blog.articles | where: 'tags', 'featured' | first
  if featured_article == blank
    assign featured_article = blog.articles.first
  endif

  assign per_page = section.settings.articles_per_page | default: 9

  # nothing_beyond_featured — true when the blog has zero articles, or
  # its only article is the one already shown by the Featured Story
  # section above (so this grid would otherwise render a lone empty
  # state with no card to actually filter/paginate against).
  assign nothing_beyond_featured = false
  if blog.articles_count == 0
    assign nothing_beyond_featured = true
  elsif blog.articles_count == 1 and featured_article != blank
    assign nothing_beyond_featured = true
  endif
-%}

{%- if nothing_beyond_featured -%}
  {%- comment -%}
    Nothing left to show below the Featured Story (either the blog is
    genuinely empty, or the one article that exists is already shown
    as the Featured Story above) — a quiet "more stories are on their
    way" state, same visual language as .ka-collection-empty (J6),
    rather than an empty grid or a broken pagination control.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="j-grid-wrap">
    <div class="j-empty is-visible">
      <h3 class="j-empty__title">More stories are on their way.</h3>
      <p class="j-empty__body">We publish quietly, and only when a story is ready. Check back soon, or explore the Journal's Featured Story above.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
{%- else -%}
  {% paginate blog.articles by per_page %}
    <div class="j-grid-wrap">
      <div class="j-grid" id="journalGrid">
        {%- for article in blog.articles -%}
          {%- unless article.id == featured_article.id -%}
            {%- render 'ka-journal-card', article: article, show_dek: true, extra_class: 'reveal-img' -%}
          {%- endunless -%}
        {%- endfor -%}
      </div>

      <div class="j-empty" id="journalEmpty">
        <h3 class="j-empty__title">More stories are on their way.</h3>
        <p class="j-empty__body">We publish quietly, and only when a story is ready. Check back soon, or explore the Journal's other notes above.</p>
      </div>

      {%- if paginate.next -%}
        <div class="j-load-more">
          <a href="{{ paginate.next.url }}" class="btn-outline-rose">View More Stories</a>
          <span class="j-load-more__count">Showing {{ paginate.current_offset | plus: blog.articles.size }} of {{ paginate.items }} stories</span>
        </div>
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>
  {% endpaginate %}
{%- endif -%}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Journal Grid",
  "tag": "div",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "articles_per_page",
      "label": "Articles per page",
      "min": 3,
      "max": 24,
      "step": 3,
      "default": 9
    }
  ],
  "presets": [
    { "name": "Journal Grid" }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
